H0.text: What name is given to a word or phrase in a computer document that can be clicked on In order to move to a related document. Hyperlink

H1.text: What name is given to a word or phrase in a computer document that can be clicked on In order to move to a related document. Linktext

H2.text: What name is given to a word or phrase in a computer document that can be clicked on In order to move to a related document. Clickword

H3.text: What name is given to a word or phrase in a computer document that can be clicked on In order to move to a related document. Href

A4.text: The text that is linked from is known as anchor text.

A5.text: Hypertext documents are interconnected by hyperlinks, which are typically activated by a mouse click, keypress set, or screen touch.
